meta:
  origin:
    producer: Jiang et al. and National Statistical Office of Korea
    title: Sex ratio at birth by birth order in South Korea and China
    description: |-
      This dataset measures the sex ratio at birth (SRB) by birth order of children (first, second, third-born, or fourth-born and higher). SRB is measured as the number of male births per 100 female births. The natural sex ratio at birth is approximately 105 male births per 100 female births.

      Data for China is sourced from Jiang et al. (2017), which examines changes in the sex ratio at birth in China using a decomposition by birth order. Data for South Korea is sourced from the National Statistical Office of Korea (NSO Korea).
    citation_full: |-
      Jiang, Q., Yu, Q., Yang, S., and Sánchez-Barricarte, J. J. (2017). Changes in sex ratio at birth in China: a decomposition by birth order. Journal of Biosocial Science, 49(6), 826–841. Available at: https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/51D48C611E5176A042FF28684041D997/S0021932016000547a.pdf/changes_in_sex_ratio_at_birth_in_china_a_decomposition_by_birth_order.pdf

      National Statistical Office of Korea (NSO Korea). Available at: http://kosis.kr/eng/statisticsList/statisticsListIndex.do?menuId=M_01_01&vwcd=MT_ETITLE&parmTabId=M_01_01&parentId=A.1;A2.2;A21.3;#A21.3.
    url_main: http://kosis.kr/eng/statisticsList/statisticsListIndex.do?menuId=M_01_01&vwcd=MT_ETITLE&parmTabId=M_01_01&parentId=A.1;A2.2;A21.3;#A21.3
    date_accessed: '2019-04-04'
    date_published: '2017'
